  "texts": [
    "Finally, the effect sizes (f 2) were calculated to assess the substantive impact of each predictor construct on the respective endogenous construct.",
    "Table 8 provides the f 2 effect size matrix for the constructs in our model.",
    "As per Cohen 89, an f 2 value of 0.02, 0.15, and 0.35 are suggestive of a small, medium, and large effect, respectively.",
    "These findings indicate that while some predictors had a more pronounced impact on certain endogenous variables, others contributed more modestly, highlighting the nuanced interplay of different factors within our model.",
    "This section delves into a detailed analysis of the study's findings, offering insights into how each result contributes to achieving our aim: exploring the impacts of various factors, including system update, memorability, and non-language barriers, on knowledge acquisition and application, and assessing how this understanding influences user perception and experience with ChatGPT."
